id: pm-qvdj
title: Add generic create/update setter for extension item fields
description: "GitHub issue #97: registerItemFields exposes custom fields to contracts/validation, but standalone extensions cannot populate those fields through pm create/update without description marker hacks. Duplicate check: pm search for registerItemFields custom fields create update field setter importer provenance found no open direct duplicate. Desired outcome: repeatable generic setter such as --field name=value on create and update, honored for declared extension item fields and reflected in contracts/help."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:cli","area:sdk",custom-fields,extensions,github-issue
created_at: "2026-06-02T15:55:03.159Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-02T22:19:39.198Z"
author: codex-gpt5
parent: pm-8jdc
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-02T21:59:49.447Z",codex-sdk-lane-20260602,"SDK/custom-item-fields lane start under pm-lwtx: reviewing current registerItemFields support and create/update mutation surface for generic extension field setters. Scope is findings and minimal implementation/test recommendations only; no claim/release."
  "2026-06-02T22:02:45.759Z",codex-sdk-lane-20260602,"SDK/custom-item-fields lane final: recommend minimal implementation: keep repeatable --field <name=value> on create/update contracts, add field?: string[] options, normalize/read it in registration-helpers, parse/coerce only active registerItemFields names, merge parsed fields into create frontMatter before applyRegisteredItemFieldDefaultsAndValidation, apply update values in mutateItem with changed_fields and stable equality, add tool/MCP param + docs/examples. Current partial work also needs PmCliErrorContext.known_fields fixed or moved into nextSteps/recovery."
  "2026-06-02T22:19:38.564Z",codex-broad-audit-20260602,"Evidence: implemented repeatable pm create/update --field name=value for active registerItemFields declarations; values are typed/coerced, undeclared fields reject with extension_item_field_unknown, contracts/tool schemas/docs updated. Passed linked test: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions-item-fields.spec.ts tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts (135 tests)."
